<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/457588-hi-all-i-just-finished-the-book-and-i">Hi all, i just finished the book, and i have a question that i had not figured out.

At the end of the book, when the mage arrives at the ceremony the writer sad that the Mage was looking for Brida and he saw the bright dot near the fire place and he went there silently and sad BRIDA, and the other half turned and told him that Brida went for a walk.......

How comes that the Mage saw the bright dot in Lorens ???</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_457588'><a id="like_count_community_question_457588" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/457588?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F68591.Brida">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/457588-hi-all-i-just-finished-the-book-and-i">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/457588-hi-all-i-just-finished-the-book-and-i">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/127131236-deepshikha"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/127131236-deepshikha">Deepshikha</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Well, this question is pretty old and I doubt the reader is even curious anymore but for anyone who searches for this question again, this is my under<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Well, this question is pretty old and I doubt the reader is even curious anymore but for anyone who searches for this question again, this is my understanding :<br /><br />The Magus sees the light over Lorens' shoulder as well because Lorens and the Magus and Brida are all each other's soulmates. He sees that Brida has already met a soulmate and is in love with him which is ultimately the reason that he lets her go; for her, because he doesn't want her heart to be pulled in two directions and for himself too, because he realizes that the night he spent with her is enough to sustain him for a lifetime. His purpose is simply more than what Brida and he together can accomplish. I think if Brida had stuck with the Path of the Sun, then maybe the Magus would've been a better choice in the end but their paths are fundamentally split now. It is my understanding that the Magus sees that he might just meet another person in the future that he will come to love. Again, if Brida had never met Lorens, she might have had her ending with the Magus. Sorry if it was too descriptive, but I just read this book and the ending, even if it was a bit sad, was also very satisfying.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
