  <span id="freeText16517684858676766273" style="display:none">The only quotes that I liked and made sense in an otherwise rambling narrative:<br /><br />"Nothing in the world is ever completely wrong. Even a stopped clock is right twice a day"<br /> ~ Brida's father (Pg.99)<br /><br />"What is now proved was once only imagin'd"<br /> ~ William Blake (Pg.174)<br /><br />"I learned that the search for God is a Dark Night, that Faith is a Dark Night. And that's hardly a surprise really, because for us each day is a dark night. None of us knows what might happen even the next minute, and yet we still go forwards. Because we trust. Because we have Faith."<br /> ~ Brida (Pg.24)</span>
