  <span id="freeText14372932245356414358" style="display:none">Ecstatic ! ! ! <br>Another wonderful book of <br><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/566.Paulo_Coelho" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1201840056p2/566.jpg" alt="Paulo Coelho" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a> <br> Paulo Coelho …...…<br><br> A wonderful piece of Fiction....<br>Adventurous!<br>Astonishing !<br>Amazing !<br>Astounding !<br>I've made peculiar plotline for this book's review-<br><br>Review :-<br><br>Author's narration was highly accomplished to touch the veins of Brida at every moment of story. <br>She was adventurer and walked on path of light as guided by her teacher and eventually after THE PARTY she became the one she wanted to be..<br>Characters:-- <br>•	Brida, 21 [1]Irish girl- Want to learn magic, Living in Dublin, astrology, tarot, and numerology<br>•	Magus, Teacher – Tradition of Sun [2]<br>•	Wicca, Teacher—Tradition of Moon <br>•	Lorren- Brida’s bf, Researcher Physics<br>•	Talbo:- warman<br>•	Loni- talbo’s wife<br><br><br>	Brida’s Inquest	<br>Inquest with	Where	Process<br>Magus	Forest(90miles)	Basic about magic Lesson 1 [3]- Faith is a Dark Night<br>Book owner	Bookstore, dubin	Give Phno. Wicca [4]<br>Wicca	At her house	Tarot Cards- 23 King of club [5] Soulmate<br>Lorren	Restaurant 	Atom, Universe<br>Wicca	Her House—Far from Dublin	Hypnotism [6]—A woman in love with…<br>Magus	Forest	Praying<br>Magus	City	HOW TO FIND SOULMATE—POINT OF LIGHT<br>Wicca	house	Cycle of moon-book of shadow Candle dagger<br>Wicca	house	Kingdom of moon—kingdom of night<br>Wicca	house	rain-making rituals [7,8]<br>Magus 	Magus house	force<br>Magus	Tall trees, cabin out in forest	Force [9]<br>Wicca	House	exercise<br>Lorren	Out cliff	Hanging out—make love<br>Wicca	Out in the city	General meeting<br>Magus	Pub 	Drank-wicca was in affair with hi—ritual of tradition of moon [10]<br>Wicca	Club	The day—the party-- The Power of the Tradition of the Moon, the Wisdom of Time<br>Alone	desert	Gift [11]<br><br><br>Concept of Magic –<br>Tradition of the Sun and <br>The Tradition of the Moon<br><br>#Brida- “Why do you want to learn about magic?” he asked.<br>“So that I can find answers to some of the questions I have<br>regarding life, so that I can learn about the occult powers, and,<br>possibly, how to travel back into the past and forward into the<br>future.”<br>#Magus- “Magic is a bridge,” he said at last, “a bridge that allows you<br>to walk from the visible world over into the invisible world, and to<br>learn the lessons of both those worlds.<br>#Magus- There are two forms,” replied the Magus. “The Tradition of<br>the Sun, which teaches the secrets through space and the world that<br>surrounds us, and the Tradition of the Moon, which teaches through<br>time and the things that are imprisoned in time’s memory.<br>**Nothing in the world is ever completely wrong, my dear,”<br>said her father, looking at the clock. “Even a stopped clock is<br>right twice a day.”<br><br>[1] I’m twenty-one,” said Brida. “If I wanted to start learning<br>ballet, I’d be considered too old.”<br>[2] I learned the Tradition of the Moon,” said the Magus, as if<br>he could read her thoughts, “but I was never a Teacher of that<br>Tradition. I am a Teacher of the Tradition of the Sun.”<br>[3] Disappointment, defeat, and despair are the tools God uses to show us the way<br>This is the first and most important lesson,” he said. “It was<br>created by a Spanish mystic who understood the meaning of faith.<br>His name was St. John of the Cross.<br>[4] The owner gave her the piece of paper. On it was a phone<br>number and a name: Wicca<br>[5] Don’t think about his physical appearance,” said Wicca, as if<br>she had read her thoughts. “Think of your Soul Mate.<br>“The Soul Mate is the first thing people learn about when<br>they want to follow the Tradition of the Moon,” she said. “Only<br>by understanding the Soul Mate can we understand how knowledge can be transmitted over time.<br>As well as dividing into two, we also find<br>ourselves. And that process of finding ourselves is called Love.<br>Because when a soul divides, it always divides into a male part and<br>a female part.<br>“That’s how the Book of Genesis explains it: the soul of Adam<br>was split in two, and Eve was born out of him.”<br>“You have a Gift, and once I know what that<br>Gift is, I might be able to teach you the Tradition of the Moon.<br>[6] At some point in one of your past lives, you set out along<br>the road of magic. I know this from the tarot visions that you<br>described.<br>[7] Both men and women<br><br>are extremely vulnerable to the force of sex, because, during sex,<br>pleasure and fear are present in equal measure.”<br>[8] This is the formula: use your five senses at all times. If they<br>all come together at the moment of orgasm, you will be accepted<br>for Initiation.<br>[9] It doesn’t matter whether you’re seeking wisdom or pleasure<br>through the force of sex, it will always be a total experience, because it’s the only experience that touches—or should touch—all<br>five senses at once. All our channels with the other person are<br>wide open<br>*At the moment of orgasm, the five senses vanish, and you<br>enter the world of magic; you can no longer see, hear, taste, touch, or smell. During those long seconds everything disappears, to be<br>replaced by ecstasy. It is exactly the same ecstasy as that attained<br>by mystics after years of renunciation and discipline.”<br>[10] A present from me to you. That is one of the eleven secret<br>temples of the Tradition of the Moon. A gift of love and gratitude for the fact that you exist and because I have waited so long<br>to find you.”<br> [11] “I consecrate you now, in this moment. Your Gift is God’s<br>instrument. May you prove to be a useful tool.”</span>
