  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_141767033" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/141767033" />
    <a title="Angee Andino" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4831839-angee-andino"><img alt="Angee Andino" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/141767033?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angee Andino" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angee Andino" href="/user/show/4831839-angee-andino">Angee Andino</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer141767033" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11799275878013547139">Paulo Coelho never ceases to put down on paper every little thing I&apos;ve ever needed to read about life. Every time I read his writing, I always take a sense of peace and better understanding with me. <br/><br/>I was given Brida this Christmas by my best friend, the person over whose shoulder I never fail to see a light, and needless to say, I was thrilled to find a Coelho book that I had not read. I rushed home the next day, picked a quiet corner of the house, and prepared myself to devour the pages, yet, </span>
  <span id="freeText11799275878013547139" style="display:none">Paulo Coelho never ceases to put down on paper every little thing I've ever needed to read about life. Every time I read his writing, I always take a sense of peace and better understanding with me. <br /><br />I was given Brida this Christmas by my best friend, the person over whose shoulder I never fail to see a light, and needless to say, I was thrilled to find a Coelho book that I had not read. I rushed home the next day, picked a quiet corner of the house, and prepared myself to devour the pages, yet, once I began to read, what I did instead was find paper and pencil and take notes. I have gone and filled page upon page of notes for this book, which inspired so much love and faith in me that I was in tears by the end. <br /><br />There is something so beautiful about the way Coelho writes about soulmates, stressing their importance and their reality while keeping from the ever-present cliche. His characters are kept simple, increasing the slot for one to insert oneself into the story. The strong theme of God and Christianity is completely enticing to me, filling me with a serenity so complete and so awe-inspiring that I felt myself grow with every page. Brida, for me, held everything I needed to start out the new year- love, magic, purpose, inspiration, and faith.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11799275878013547139" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

